  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Kenya Emergency Drought Response (PACIDA)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">-Improved access to life-saving food   and meeting basic needs through provision of unconditional cash through mobile money for vulnerable households 
-Save and sustain  core breeding  livestock assets of drought affected HHs
-Improved access to life saving food through provision of food vouchers
-Improved quality of response through access to safe and responsive feedback mechanism</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Output 1: Emergency cash transfer to affected households &#x2013; 600 households (3600people) receiving 3000 KES on a monthly basis 
Output 2: Food voucher distribution to affected households- 600 households (3600 people) receiving food voucher worth KES 3000 on a monthly basis.
Output 3: Save and support livestock assets of affected households- 800 breeding stock ( approx. 240 people) 
Output 4: Feedback reports on community feedback on access, quality and effectiveness of response (7440).</narrative>
  </description>
